The paper deals with image manipulation and detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of machine learning algorithms for detecting manipulations suggests that it could also belong to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of metadata for training the model, which could fall under cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a new learning algorithm, which could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
